      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) directly map to regulatory submission requirements and clinical performance endpoints.",
      "rationale": "The three selected QoIs are the primary endpoints specified in ASTM F1717 and referenced in FDA guidance for spinal implant 510(k) submissions. Stiffness and yield force are directly linked to implant fatigue life and surgical performance claims."
